{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "[Full Name]",
  "honorificPrefix": "[Dr., Prof., Mr., Ms.]",
  "honorificSuffix": "[MD, PhD, MBA, JD]",
  "givenName": "[First Name]",
  "familyName": "[Last Name]",
  "gender": "[Male/Female]",
  "birthDate": "[1985-01-15]",
  "url": "https://yourdomain.com/about/person-name",
  "image": {
    "@type": "ImageObject",
    "url": "https://yourdomain.com/images/person-headshot.jpg",
    "width": 400,
    "height": 400
  },
  "jobTitle": "[Board-Certified Physician, Professor, CEO]",
  "description": "[1-2 sentence professional bio highlighting expertise and experience]",
  "worksFor": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "[Organization Name]",
    "url": "https://organization.com",
    "sameAs": "https://linkedin.com/company/organization"
  },
  "affiliation": [
    {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "[Stanford School of Medicine]"
    },
    {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "[American Academy of Dermatology]"
    }
  ],
  "alumniOf": [
    {
      "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
      "name": "[Harvard Medical School]",
      "sameAs": "https://hms.harvard.edu"
    },
    {
      "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
      "name": "[Yale University]"
    }
  ],
  "sameAs": [
    "https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=ABC123",
    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-2345-6789",
    "https://linkedin.com/in/person-name",
    "https://twitter.com/person-handle",
    "https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q87654321"
  ],
  "knowsAbout": [
    "Dermatology",
    "Regenerative Medicine",
    "Longevity Science",
    "Aesthetic Medicine"
  ],
  "award": [
    "Top Physician, City Magazine 2024",
    "Research Excellence Award, Medical Association 2023",
    "40 Under 40, Business Journal 2022"
  ],
  "hasCredential": {
    "@type": "EducationalOccupationalCredential",
    "credentialCategory": "Board Certification",
    "recognizedBy": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "American Board of Internal Medicine"
    }
  },
  "colleague": [
    {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "[Colleague Name]",
      "url": "https://yourdomain.com/about/colleague"
    }
  ],
  "contactPoint": {
    "@type": "ContactPoint",
    "telephone": "+1-555-123-4567",
    "email": "person@yourdomain.com",
    "contactType": "Professional"
  }
}

/*
USAGE NOTES:

1. E-E-A-T Signals (+40% Citation Boost):
   - honorificSuffix: CRITICAL - Add ALL credentials (MD, PhD, MBA, etc.)
   - affiliation: Link to recognized institutions
   - alumniOf: Show educational background
   - worksFor: Connect to authoritative organizations
   - sameAs: Link to Google Scholar, ORCID, LinkedIn
   - hasCredential: Specify board certifications

2. Credentials Format:
   Medical:
   - "MD, PhD, FAAD" (American Academy of Dermatology Fellow)
   - "DO, MBA, FACP" (American College of Physicians Fellow)
   - "DDS, MS" (Dental specialists)

   Academic:
   - "PhD, MBA"
   - "JD, LLM"
   - "EdD, MA"

   Professional:
   - "CPA, CFA"
   - "PE, MBA"
   - "PMP, CISSP"

3. Image Requirements:
   - Professional headshot
   - Square ratio (400Ã—400px minimum)
   - High quality, well-lit
   - Professional attire
   - Solid or simple background
   - Consistent across platforms

4. sameAs (Authority Links):
   Priority order:
   1. Google Scholar (academics, researchers)
   2. ORCID (researchers, scientists)
   3. LinkedIn (all professionals)
   4. Twitter/X (public figures)
   5. Wikipedia/Wikidata (notable individuals)
   6. Professional association profiles
   7. University faculty pages

5. knowsAbout (Expertise):
   - List 3-10 areas of expertise
   - Use recognized field names
   - Match content topics
   - Include specializations
   - Align with industry terminology

6. Awards and Recognition:
   - Recent awards (last 5 years)
   - Notable achievements
   - Industry recognition
   - Publications and patents
   - Speaking engagements

KNOWLEDGE GRAPH OPTIMIZATION:

Google Knowledge Panel Requirements:
1. Dedicated profile page on website
2. Person schema on profile page
3. Active LinkedIn profile (complete)
4. Google Scholar profile (if academic)
5. Professional headshot (consistent)
6. Author bylines on articles
7. External mentions and citations

Entity Recognition Signals:
- Consistent name usage everywhere
- Professional profiles linked (sameAs)
- Author schema on all articles
- Credentials displayed
- Institutional affiliations
- Published works
- Media mentions

AUTHOR ATTRIBUTION (Articles):

On each article page, link to person:
{
  "@type": "Article",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "@id": "https://yourdomain.com/about/person-name#person"
  }
}

On person profile page, use full schema with #person ID:
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "@id": "https://yourdomain.com/about/person-name#person",
  "name": "Dr. Full Name",
  ...
}

